 created spaces for their individual concerns.Copub: Center for Black Music Research  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMusicxHistory and criticismx20th centuryxCuba. 0aMusicxPolitical aspectsxCuba. 0aMusicxPolitical aspectszCuba. 0aMusiczCubay20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSocialism and music. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Pop Vocal.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aafrican diaspora.  aart and music.  ablack music.  acuba.  acuban history.  acuban revolution.  acubans.  acultural historians.  acultural history.  adance styles.  aethnomusicologists.  aethnomusicology.  afolklore.  ainternational relations.  alatin american studies.  amusic and culture.  amusic and politics.  amusic historians.  amusic history.  amusical styles.  amusicians.  apolitical history.  apolitical revolution.  areligious traditions.  asocialism.  asoviet union.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093946240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939462423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520939462/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles